description:
Lines 286 and 295 log the full relay URL from the CLI --relay flag:

  info!("connected via SOCKS5 tunnel to {url}");
  info!("connected to {url}");

If a user runs:
  nie --relay "wss://user:pass@relay.example.com/ws" --proxy socks5h://127.0.0.1:9050 chat

The credentials leak to process logs, RUST_LOG output, journalctl, and any centralized logging system.

Mitigation: Strip user:pass from the relay URL before logging. Use url.host().unwrap_or("unknown") instead:

  info!("connected via SOCKS5 tunnel to {}", url_without_credentials);

This leaks no sensitive data while still providing useful debugging context (hostname + scheme).
